I've seen some concepts thrown around about a (Linux) kernel patch to disallow filenames which contain unprintable characters. I approve of them.<p>With regard to why this matters, it's not uncommon for badly written scripts to interpolate filenames directly into commands. Consider this Perl fragment:<p><pre><code>  $sessionFiles = `ls /tmp/session_*`;
  system("rm -f $sessionFiles");
</code></pre>
and what it would do with a file called:<p><pre><code>  "/tmp/session_blah; chmod +s"</code></pre>
